    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect LDPC encoder indices causing wrong parity bits\n\n### Summary\nThe AVX2-optimized LDPC encoder for Zc=320 contained several indices that were not properly scaled down by a factor of 2 compared to the 128-bit reference version. This caused the encoder to access incorrect memory locations during parity bit computation, leading to wrong channel coding output.\n\nThe issue was most noticeable when encoding transport blocks with sizes that map to Zc=320 lifting size, where decoded data would contain bit errors after passing through the physical layer simulator.\n\nRoot cause was incomplete conversion from the 128-bit version to the AVX2 version - some array indices were left at their original values instead of being halved to account for the wider 256-bit SIMD registers processing twice as much data per operation.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_encoder/ldpc320_byte.c`: Corrected multiple array indices by dividing by 2 to match AVX2 register width.\n- Fixed specific indices: 14049\u21927024, 13260\u21926660, 14066\u21927033, 14064\u21927032\n- Verified alignment with 128-bit reference implementation pattern\n\n"
}